                    <p class="text-slate-700 text-sm"><strong>GaN vs Silicon: which is better?</strong> GaN (Gallium Nitride) chargers outperform silicon chargers on every metric that matters: <strong>40-50% smaller</strong> volume, <strong>30% cooler</strong> operation, <strong>95%+ efficiency</strong> (vs 85%), <strong>5+ year lifespan</strong> (vs 2-3), and support for up to <strong>240W PD 3.1</strong>. Silicon's only advantage is lower component cost at very low wattages (<20W). For any charger above 30W — especially if it leaves your house — GaN is the better choice.</p>
